  "text": "In addition to the low density of built environment, Franklin has vast amounts of public open spaces, with approximately 47 hectares easily accessible and spread throughout the whole suburb (Figure 3) . With a population of 6419 people, the amount of green space, in the form of natural landscape, recreational park and natural grassland (Figure 4) , is more than double the recommended Australian Standard of 3 ha every 1000 people [CITATION_1] . This means that there is enough space for significant increase in population. ",
